{"sequence":43,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T22:08:02.394781325Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-c0e0b581","body":"In `claim_bead_in_br` (src/cli/project.rs:822-832), when `update_bead_status` fails and `load_bead_detail` also fails, the code falls through to the generic error at line 833 which wraps `update_error`. However, `load_bead_detail` can fail for various reasons (network, br binary unavailable, JSON parse error). The `update_error` is reported but the `load_bead_detail` failure is silently swallowed. Consider logging the `load_bead_detail` error at debug/trace level so operators can diagnose why the fallback check failed, especially in scenarios where `br show` itself is broken.","dedup_key":"a6e3cf1d6cf6bdce412196805b4f3b8d6e7fbd72f741e382e9c900669e6bb090","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408204915","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":44,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T22:08:02.404132103Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-405b8bde","body":"In `src/cli/project.rs` at lines 822-825, do not `return Ok(())` from the \"already in_progress and this is our own prior claim\" branch. That branch currently exits before the `br.sync_flush()` call at lines 838-844, so a retry after `br update` succeeded but `br sync --flush-only` did not will report success without ever flushing the claim into the `.beads` export that `bv` reads. Keep the idempotent-own-claim detection, but continue into `sync_flush()` so the bead actually disappears from ready triage on recovery.","dedup_key":"05b875fb613680778fbf7a3021cce1758c9f1778f8acadac466759554d249274","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408204915","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":45,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T22:08:02.413421636Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-6d39965e","body":"In `src/cli/project.rs` at lines 413-464, handle failures from `milestone_controller::sync_controller_task_claimed` the same way project-creation failures are handled at lines 425-450. Right now the code creates the Ralph project and leaves the bead claimed in `br`, then immediately returns on any controller-write/alignment error without transitioning the controller to `needs_operator` or rolling back the new project. That leaves an orphan claimed bead/project pair and allows duplicate project creation on retry. Wrap the controller-link step in explicit recovery logic (at minimum transition to `needs_operator`; ideally also avoid leaving the newly created project live if the link cannot be recorded).","dedup_key":"8aa2e67ea81c0db50a43ed87a55671a44c76b3d087ec927d49ab766f302ea7d9","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408204915","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
