{"sequence":64,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T22:27:48.921952816Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-3d3a1ecd","body":"In `is_our_active_bead` (src/cli/project.rs:892-900), the check `ctrl.state == MilestoneControllerState::Claimed` is too strict for idempotent retries. After a `sync_flush` failure, `handle_create_from_bead` transitions the controller to `NeedsOperator` (line 390-406). On retry, the bead is locally `in_progress` (br update succeeded earlier) but the controller is now in `NeedsOperator` with the same `active_bead_id`. Since `is_our_active_bead` only accepts `Claimed`, it returns `false`, causing the retry to fail with 'claimed by another process' instead of being idempotent. Fix: also accept `NeedsOperator` state in the `is_our_active_bead` check, e.g. `matches!(ctrl.state, MilestoneControllerState::Claimed | MilestoneControllerState::NeedsOperator)`.","dedup_key":"894a0015e9132a197bc8a1f70ddef157c79465712944c3a28f171e5ea62ba9ca","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408204915","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":65,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T22:27:48.930429842Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-ffaa74f7","body":"`claim_bead_in_br` misclassifies another operator's claim as an idempotent retry. In `src/cli/project.rs:831-859` and `src/cli/project.rs:892-899`, the fallback treats `br update <bead> --status=in_progress` failing with the bead already `in_progress` as success whenever the controller is already `claimed` for that bead. But `select_next_milestone_bead` writes that `claimed` controller state before any `br update` happens (`src/cli/run.rs:589-599`), so this check does not prove we previously claimed the bead in `br`; it only proves we selected it locally. If another operator claims the bead after selection but before our update, this branch will still proceed to create a Ralph project instead of moving to `needs_operator`. Remove this fallback or replace it with stronger post-claim evidence, and add a test for the \"selection already marked claimed, but another process won the race\" case.","dedup_key":"d9d701246020a29696b30739c6c353f41ade1c2b33e98ccdebb2a26863df6a63","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408204915","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
